<!-----begin section: Software -->

<tr>
   <td width=3D"15%" valign=3D"top">
      <i>Software</i>
   </td>
   <td width=3D"85%" valign=3D"top">
      The <i>F</i>-test for equality of two variances is
      available in many general purpose statistical
      software programs.  Both=20
      <a href=3D"https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/section3/eda3=
59.dp">Dataplot code</a> and=20
      <a href=3D"https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/section3/eda3=
59.r">R code</a> can be used to generate=20
      the analyses in this section.  These scripts use the
      <a href=3D"https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/datasets/AUTO83B.=
DAT">AUTO83B.DAT</a> data file.

   </td>
</tr>

